& [ZetaOscilloscope] is the corrected finite phasor instrument for visualizing prime-power contributions to the logarithmic derivative structure of zeta
  + [conversation_uuid] is 42c4c9ad-e962-4f5f-85ab-ed21ff7e118f
  + [canonical_specification_uuid] is d76e9557-27ac-467e-ab46-4642c3879d48
  + [source_snapshot_uuid] is a6fec933-1869-415c-90b7-c1c324dacf99
  + [dictated_source_document] is platform/source_documents/2026-05-19_zeta_oscilloscope_definition/Dictated_Zeta_Oscilloscope_Source.sop
  + [solution_uuid] is 235c3796-8113-4272-bb08-7b6944bd53b9
  + [instrument_name] is Zeta Oscilloscope
  + [alias] is Lambda-Oscilloscope
  + [height_parameter] is t
  + [line_parameter] is sigma
  + [critical_default] is sigma = 1/2
  + [cutoff_parameter] is N
  + [window_function] is W_N(n), an optional finite cutoff smoothing weight
  + [default_window_function] is hard cutoff W_N(n) = 1 for n <= N and 0 otherwise
  + [recommended_smooth_window] is a taper on n/N used to reduce cutoff ringing when visual continuity matters
  + [von_mangoldt_function] is Lambda(n)
  + [prime_power_rule] is Lambda(n) = log(p) when n = p^k for prime p and integer k >= 1
  + [zero_rule] is Lambda(n) = 0 when n is not a prime power
  + [complex_parameter] is s = sigma + i t
  + [corrected_phase] is exp(-i t log(n))
  + [corrected_angular_velocity] is log(n)
  + [corrected_series] is E_{sigma,N,W}(t) = sum over n from 1 to N of Lambda(n) n^{-sigma} W_N(n) exp(-i t log(n))
  + [unsmoothed_series] is E_{sigma,N}(t) = sum over n from 1 to N of Lambda(n) n^{-sigma} exp(-i t log(n))
  + [visual_trace] is t maps to (Re(E_{sigma,N,W}(t)), Im(E_{sigma,N,W}(t)))
  + [analytic_relation] is the finite Dirichlet-polynomial analogue of -zeta_prime(s) divided by zeta(s)
  + [zetabrot_readout] is finite cutoff visualization of the Lambda-Zetabrot Fourier layer
  + [rh_relevance] is strongest when sigma = 1/2 because the trace is sampled on the critical line s = 1/2 + i t
  + [source_authority_state] is processed_to_satisfaction_for_definition_only

  = must: use exp(-i t log(n)) as the zeta-aligned phase term
  = must: treat each nonzero Lambda(n) term as a prime-power oscillator
  = must: weight the n term by Lambda(n) n^{-sigma} and optional W_N(n)
  = must: define angular velocity as log(n), not n
  = must: preserve finite cutoff N as part of the computational instrument
  = must: distinguish hard cutoff from smoothed cutoff
  = must: identify sigma = 1/2 as critical-line normalization
  = must: identify the finite trace as an exploratory visualization, not a proof of RH
  = must: preserve the source lineage from Euler's Mirror through Zeta Ear as conceptual ancestry when referenced
  - never: use exp(-i t n) for the zeta-aligned definition unless defining a separate non-zeta variant
  - never: claim normal convergence of the infinite von Mangoldt Dirichlet series on sigma = 1/2
  - never: present finite cutoff traces as direct RH verification

& [OscillatorTerm] is one active phasor in the Zeta Oscilloscope
  + [term_index] is n
  + [prime_base] is p when n is p^k
  + [power] is k when n is p^k
  + [amplitude] is Lambda(n) n^{-sigma} W_N(n)
  + [phase] is -t log(n)
  + [angular_velocity] is log(n)
  + [phasor] is amplitude times exp(i phase)

  ? [n is prime power]
    = must: include term with Lambda(n) = log(p)

  ? [n is not prime power]
    = must: exclude term because Lambda(n) = 0

& [WindowDiscipline] is the finite cutoff policy
  + [hard_cutoff] is W_N(n) = 1 for n <= N
  + [smooth_cutoff] is W(n/N) with values near 1 at small n and decaying toward 0 near the cutoff
  + [cutoff_ringing] is visual artifact caused by abrupt truncation

  = may: use hard_cutoff for simple finite experiments
  = should: use smooth_cutoff when comparing visual continuity across N
  = must: label the selected window policy in any visualization
  - never: hide smoothing as if it were part of the von Mangoldt function itself

& [VisualizationContract] is the buildable UI shape implied by the definition
  + [primary_surface] is a complex-plane oscilloscope trace
  + [secondary_surface] is a phasor stack or spectrum view of prime-power terms
  + [controls] are sigma, N, t range, t step, window policy, and animation rate
  + [telemetry] is current t, Re(E), Im(E), magnitude, active term count, sigma, N, and window policy
  + [provenance] is dictated_source_document and corrected canonical definition

  = must: plot Re(E) against Im(E) as t varies
  = should: expose prime-power term contributions when the goal is interpretation
  = should: warn when sigma <= 1/2 and the user interprets finite traces too strongly

& [CorrectionLedger] is the explicit repair from source sketch to canonical definition
  + [source_phase] is exp(-i t n)
  + [source_angular_velocity] is n
  + [corrected_phase] is exp(-i t log(n))
  + [corrected_angular_velocity] is log(n)
  + [repair_reason] is n^{-it} equals exp(-i t log(n)) for zeta Dirichlet terms
  + [preserved_source_intent] is complex-plane waveform driven by prime-power oscillators

  = must: preserve source_intent while correcting phase semantics
  = must: treat the source sketch as untuned rather than discarded

& [AcceptanceCriteria] is the completion standard for the definition
  + [canonical_file] is platform/refinement/Zeta_Oscilloscope.sop
  + [source_file] is platform/source_documents/2026-05-19_zeta_oscilloscope_definition/Dictated_Zeta_Oscilloscope_Source.sop
  + [phase_corrected] is exp(-i t log(n))
  + [lambda_defined] is von Mangoldt prime-power rule present
  + [finite_cutoff_defined] is N and optional W_N(n) present
  + [rh_boundary_defined] is sigma = 1/2 identified as relevant but not proof-bearing
  + [correction_ledger_present] is source fault and repair visible

